cisc275.group3.utility

Interface ConstructHeron

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SceneTutorial

    public interface ConstructHeron
    Interface to simplify the construction of heron objects. This code used to be within SceneWetland.java, but is transitioned into an interface to reduce code size and increase extensibility.

    ConstructHeron.java

    Author:
    Jon

    • Method Detail

      • constructLeftHeron

        static ObjectHeron constructLeftHeron(int depth,
                                      int type,
                                      double x,
                                      double y,
                                      boolean land,
                                      boolean hasLand)
        Returns a constructed Beta Heron object. This heron will move left
        Parameters:
        depth - int-heron depth
        type - int-heron type [0,1] (0 = landed , 1 = flying)
        x - double-x-axis location
        y - double-y-axis location
        land - boolean-determines if the heron has landed (is not moving)
        hasLand - boolean-determines if the heron has ever landed. If it has landed, it will not land again
        Returns:
        BetaHeron
